=== TASK ===
# Narrative Drill-down

## Overview
You are building the Narrative Drill-down experience for the Gbox360 platform. This feature set delivers explainability and auditability for Investor Perception Index (IPI) movements. It enables users to understand why a narrative contributed to an IPI movement by linking each narrative contribution to underlying NarrativeEvents and raw source payloads. The solution includes a drill-down page, an explainability UI, a dashboard workspace, and a Company Detail & IPI view. All code must be runtime-safe against null/undefined values, guard array operations, and initialize array state properly as described in the project’s mandatory coding standards.

---

## Page Description (Full Detail)

What this page is:
- Narrative Drill-down: a deep-dive page that explains why a specific narrative contributed to an IPI movement. Each contribution links to the corresponding NarrativeEvents and exposes the raw source payloads for audit.

Goals:
- Provide end-to-end narrative provenance from a high-level movement to individual NarrativeEvents and raw payloads.
- Enable users to explore the trajectory of a narrative via a replay/timeline, with an authority & credibility breakdown, and provenance artifacts.
- Surface an export artifact that bundles the narrative’s provenance, impact score breakdown, and related raw payloads.

Connected features:
- IPI Explainability & Drill-down UI: UI patterns to explain movements and provide direct drill-down into NarrativeEvents and raw payloads.
- Dashboard: Primary user workspace after login with IPI summary, directional change, top narratives, quick search, and recent activity.
- Company Detail & IPI: Focused view for a selected company and time window with full IPI breakdown (Narrative / Credibility / Risk), full narrative list, timeline, and raw payload access.

UI elements and how they need to look:
- Narrative summary panel: high-level explanation of the narrative’s trajectory, key drivers, and timestamped milestones.
- Contributing events list: sorted by impact score (highest first), each row shows source, timestamp, speaker role heuristic, a concise excerpt, and a direct “View Event” action.
- Event detail panel: shows full raw text, link to the original source, and associated topics/tags; includes a copy-to-clipboard for raw payload.
- Authority & Credibility panel: multi-segment breakdown (analyst, media, retail) with weighted contributions, and credibility proxy signals (language strength, repetition, etc.).
- Replay & timeline slider: interactive control to scrub through narrative occurrences over time with synchronized event highlights.
- Export audit artifact: a button that generates a downloadable artifact (JSON/ZIP) including provenance chain, score breakdown, and linked raw payloads.
- Visual guidance: warm neutral background with pastel tiles, cards with soft shadows, rounded corners, and accessible hover states. Maintain consistent typography and grid rhythm across all sub-pages.

Visual style (consistent across connected pages):
- Color palette and typography as specified in the Visual Style section (below).
- Ensure responsive behavior for 2–3 column layouts on wide screens and 1–2 on smaller viewports.
- Ensure accessibility: sufficient color contrast, focus outlines, keyboard navigability.

---

## Components to Build

1) NarrativeDrilldownPage
- Purpose: Orchestrates the drill-down view for a selected narrative.
- Props/State: narrativeId, companyId, timeWindow; internal states for narrative, events, credibility, timeline, and export artifact readiness.
- Data flow: fetch narrative metadata, fetch related NarrativeEvents (guarantee null-safety), fetch raw payloads; pass data to child components.
- UI: narrative summary, authority/credibility panel, contributing events list, event detail panel, timeline replay, export button.

2) NarrativeEventList
- Purpose: List of NarrativeEvents contributing to the selected narrative.
- Data: Array<NarrativeEvent>.
- Features: sort by impactScore, show excerpt, timestamp, source, and role heuristic; provide “View Event” modal/side panel and a quick link to raw payload.
- Interaction: click to highlight in timeline, expand/collapse, keyboard accessible.

3) EventDetailPanel
- Purpose: Show full raw text, source link, topics/tags, and copy raw payload.
- Data: NarrativeEvent + associated rawPayload.
- Interaction: copy to clipboard, open external source link, show version metadata.

4) AuthorityCredibilityPanel
- Purpose: Display authority weighting breakdown and credibility proxy signals.
- Data: authorityWeights = {analyst, media, retail}, credibilitySignals.
- Interaction: hover tooltips explaining each weight, dynamic color intensity by weight.

5) TimelineReplay
- Purpose: Visual timeline scrubber for narrative occurrences.
- Data: array of events with timestamps; currentTimeIndex.
- Interaction: drag scrubber, play/pause, scrub to specific event, synchronized highlight in EventList.

6) ExportArtifactButton
- Purpose: Generate and download an audit artifact bundle.
- Data: narrativeId + related events + rawPayloads + score breakdown.
- Output: downloadable JSON/ZIP containing provenance, timestamps, sources, and payloads.

7) DashboardSummaryCard (for Dashboard page)
- Purpose: Present IPI summary for selected company/time window; shows current score, direction, top narratives, quick search, and recent activity.
- Data: IPI score object, topNarratives array, recentActivity.
- UI: summary bar, mini-dials or directional indicators, narrative chips.

8) CompanyDetailIPISection
- Purpose: Full IPI breakdown (Narrative, Credibility, Risk) for a selected company/time window.
- Data: breakdown components, full narrative list, timeline, raw payload access control.
- UI: tabs or segmented controls to switch breakdown view; list of narratives with quick actions to view events and payloads.

9) APIConnectionLayer (Frontend)
- Purpose: Centralized API layer to fetch: narrative details, narrative events, raw payloads, credibility signals, IPI metrics.
- Safety: Always validate responses with Array.isArray and nullish coalescing; guard all array methods.

10) DataGuard & Utils
- Purpose: Utilities for null-safety (guard arrays, defaults), date formatting, cloning payloads, and safe destructuring with defaults.

---

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Routing:
  - /dashboard -> DashboardSummary
  - /narratives/:narrativeId/drilldown -> NarrativeDrilldownPage
